WARRI – Engr Austin Avuru Chairman AA Holdings, on Thursday, tasked the management of the Federal University of Petroleum Resources Effurun (FUPRE ) Delta State to stand firm to close gaps created in research, training and development as a result of the gradual divestment of the international oil companies ( IOC) from Nigeria. Austin Avuru a top and key player in the Petroleum industry made this observation today as the guest speaker of the 15th Founders Day Celebration 3rd Lecture Series held at FUPRE Hall one The Petroleum guru who spoke on the theme titled, “Expanding The Frontier of Petroleum Education Through Stakeholders Participation” noted that with the exit of the lOC’s and their well-established training organizations, the Federal University of Petroleum Resources, Effurun (FUPRE ) has to step out of the crowd of regular Nigerian Universities and step in to fill the vacuum being created by the failure of NNPC Research and Development Division and the withdrawal of the lOC’s from the sphere. Austin Avuru stressed that FUPRE has to become the one step institution for tertiary and post-tertiary specialized training for the Nigerian Oil and Gas industry and the Energy industry in the future which is the context and basis on which he fully aligned with the University dream and focus on stakeholders Participation. While commending the laudable strides of Engr Prof. Akpofure Rim- Rukeh the Vice-Chancellor and his Management team Austin Avuru urged FUPRE as a specialized great citadel of learning to streamline their current NUC Curriculum into relevant Science, Engineering, Commercial, Environmental and other associated faculties and lean on close collaboration with industry stakeholders to build FUPRE into a world-class centre of excellence for Petroleum Education in Africa and even across the continental shelf. According to him , if FUPRE step up the game, Research and Development funds will come abundantly from industrial players adding that the University must continue to acknowledge itself as the centre for relevant knowledge acquisition and leverage into working with key industry stakeholders like the Oil Producers Trade Section of the Lagos Chapter of Commerce OPTS, the lndependent Petroleum Producers Group, IPPG , the Petroleum Technology Development Fund PTDF, and NNPC which will ever remain willing and principal collaborators in the business of Petroleum Education While making his summàtion Austin Avuru the Prolific guest speaker suggested that FUPRE should establisha college of specialized oil and gas training as a semi-autonomous faculty which will be funded by the industry as critical stakeholders. Engr Prof Rim-Rukeh the Vice-Chancellor of the University earlier in his welcome /keynote address titled, ”FUPRE in Brief” spoke about the mission and vision of the First African University of Petroleum that ranks sixth in the world as academic excellence and innovation. POLL Engr Prof Akpofure the erudite academia stated that the University guiding philosophy remains the promotion and advancement of knowledge and the production of graduates who are technopreneurs with concern for the promotion of environmentally friendly technological solutions in the practice of their profession. He summarized the core values of FUPRE as Contemporary, Relevance,Excellence, Adaptive, Trailblazing, ingenious, Vintage and Entrepreneurial, When put together it forms what FUPRE calls the creative core values he said. Engr Prof Akpofure appreciated all the pioneer staff of the for the various sacrifice they made for the survival of the University, he commended the effort of five students,the stars who won the inter University Science Quiz, the royal fathers present, the host Community and all invited guests. Some Prominent senior citizens who played a strategic role in their immense contributions to the growth and development of FUPRE in the 15 years of its existence were honoured.The list of the Awardees includes Chiéf TA Okpoko (SAN), Chief TuesdayOloge, HRM Dr Emmanuel Ekemejewan Sideso JP Abe l the Ovie of Uvwie kingdom, Chief Kenneth Gbagi, former minister of State for Education, and Chiéf Peter Asagba, MD/CEO Casa Depedro. The two immediate host Communities, Ugbomro and Eterigbi were recognized and honoured for their peaceful disposition. Others who made the list on a posthumous category were late Major General E O Obada( rtd)Late Senator Prof Adegor Eferakeya, and Late Senator Pius Ehwerido who did their very best in the success story of FUPRE.